   {:e #blake3 "a16716ef5456159d9cf339dfc23d29be15f41ca79c5704fe39a47d256d8388e6" :a :spec/statement :v "LiveStore tracks a dirty flag. write_tx() sets dirty=true and updates the in-memory Store but does NOT serialize store.bin on every call. Serialization happens at exactly two points: (1) explicit LiveStore::flush() call, (2) LiveStore::drop() (process exit). This ensures at most one serialization per process lifetime regardless of the number of writes. Crash safety preserved by C1: txn files are fsynced to disk on every write_tx, so the next LiveStore::open() reconstructs the full state via incremental apply even if store.bin is stale." :op :assert}
